<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7792ffcb-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s430f–7"><num value="430f–7">§ 430f–7.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In sections 430f–6 to 430f–12 of this title:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id7792ffcc-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s430f–7/1"><num value="1" class="bold">(1)</num><heading class="bold"> Map</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Map” means the map entitled “Park Boundary-Corinth Unit”, numbered 304A/80009, and dated April 2007.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id7792ffcd-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s430f–7/2"><num value="2" class="bold">(2)</num><heading class="bold"> Park</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Park” means the Shiloh National Military Park.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id7792ffce-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s430f–7/3"><num value="3" class="bold">(3)</num><heading class="bold"> Secretary</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id7792ffcf-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s430f–7/4"><num value="4" class="bold">(4)</num><heading class="bold"> Unit</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Unit” means the Corinth Unit of Shiloh National Military Park established under <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s430f–8">section 430f–8 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id7792ffd0-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/271/s3">Pub. L. 106–271, § 3</ref>, <date date="2000-09-22">Sept. 22, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/793">114 Stat. 793</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/110/161/dF/tI/s127/1">Pub. L. 110–161, div. F, title I, § 127(1)</ref>, <date date="2007-12-26">Dec. 26, 2007</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/121/2122">121 Stat. 2122</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7792ffd1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7792ffd2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7792ffd3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2007—Par. (1). <ref href="/us/pl/110/161">Pub. L. 110–161</ref> substituted “304A/80009, and dated April 2007” for “304/80,007, and dated October 1998”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
